# Folder Structure & Import Rules

## Import Path Aliases

Always use `@/` path aliases — never relative paths that escape the current feature module.

```typescript
import { Task, Priority } from "@/core/tasks"             // feature barrel
import type { CreateTaskDTO } from "@/core/tasks"          // types from barrel
import { DomainError } from "@/core/shared"                // shared cross-cutting
import { Button } from "@/components/ui"                   // UI primitives
import { TaskList } from "@/features/tasks"                // frontend feature
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"                           // utilities
import type { ApiResponse } from "@/types"                 // shared types
```

## Import Rules by Layer

| From | Can Import | Cannot Import |
|------|-----------|---------------|
| API Route | `@/core/shared/.../dependencies` + `@/core/[feature]` (types) | Feature infrastructure directly |
| Frontend Feature | `@/core/[feature]` (types) + dependencies (actions) | Another feature's internals |
| Use Case | Own feature's domain + `@/core/shared` | Other features, infrastructure |
| Repository | Own feature's domain + application | Other features |
| Feature A | **Never** Feature B's infrastructure | Use `@/core/shared` instead |

## Barrel Exports

Every module needs an `index.ts` barrel export. External consumers import **only** from the barrel, never from internal paths.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Task } from "@/core/tasks"

// ❌ WRONG — importing internal path
import { Task } from "@/core/tasks/domain/task.entity"
```
